The paper discusses the use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for medical image analysis, specifically for semantic segmentation of polyps from colonoscopy images. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories. The paper also discusses uncertainty estimation and model interpretability, which are topics related to Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper focuses on medical image analysis, which suggests that it could belong to the Medical Imaging (cs.MED) category. Finally, the paper evaluates and enhances several architectures of Fully Convolutional Networks (FCNs), which is a topic related to Information Retrieval (cs.IR).
